$ SQLite: date and time related functions

SQLite has five functions that are related to date and time:
  • `time     (     expr, …)`
  • `date     (     expr, …)`
  • `datetime (     expr, …)`
  • `julianday(     expr, …)`
  • `strftime (fmt, expr, …)`

The first four differ from the last one that the use a default format for the returned value while `strftime` allows to explicitely define the
returned format.
-
The formats used for the four functions is displayed in the following table:

table { lll
   `time     (   , str, … )` ☰ `%H:%M:%S`            ☰ `hh:mm:ss`
   `date     (   , str, … )` ☰ `%Y-%m-%d`            ☰ `yyyy-mm-dd`
   `datetime (   , str, … )` ☰ `%H:%M:%S` `%Y-%M-%d` ☰ `yyyy-mm-dd hh:mm:ss`
   `julianday(   , str, … )` ☰ `%J`                  ☰  dddd.dddd
table }

Thus, the following to expressions are equivalent:
code {
date('now')
strftime('%Y-%m-%d', 'now')
code }

